Governor of Katsina State, Aminu Bello Masari has warned residents of Daura local government area to comply with the stay-at-home order of his administration because Daura is now in dangerous transmission stage of COVID -19. He stated this at the commissioning and handing over of the fully-equipped COVID-19 isolation centre donated by the National Lottery Trust Fund to the state government, yesterday, in Daura. He said that community transmission is the dangerous stage of contraction and warned the people to remain indoor. He said: “So, you all have a responsibility to protect the health of your neighbour. It is not about I but we and the whole world is undergoing severe stress because of this disease. “People should stay at home, there is lockdown in Daura and now we have entered the dangerous stage of transmission- community transmission. What we started having were people coming from other country or visitors from Nigeria, but what we are having now is community transmission and that is what we have in Daura. “So, we have the capacity, we have the determination and we have the political will to force you in, but we are appealing that in your best interest stay at home.” Earlier, the minister of Special Duty and Inter-governmental Affairs, Hon. George Akume, thanked the lottery club for the gesture, urging them to replicate same to other states. He further commended  President Muhammadu Buhari’s effort in putting measures to curtail the pandemic in Nigeria and called all citizens to equally obey the lockdown order which is the best way to curb the spread.